# WXT reads .env from THIS directory (apps/extension), not the repo
# root and not apps/backend — copy this file to apps/extension/.env,
# not anywhere else, or the extension build will never see it.
#
# This is baked in at BUILD time, not read at runtime — changing it
# requires restarting `wxt dev` (dev server) or re-running `wxt build`
# (production build) for the new value to take effect. Editing .env
# alone with an already-built/already-running extension does nothing.

# Realtime server URL the extension connects to.
#
# - Same machine only: http://localhost:3001 (the default if this is
#   left unset — see lib/realtime.ts)
# - Testing across devices on the same network (phone + laptop, two
#   laptops, etc.): use your machine's mDNS hostname or LAN IP instead
#   of localhost, e.g. http://your-machine-name.local:3001 or
#   http://192.168.1.5:3001 — "localhost" always means "this same
#   device" to every device, which is why cross-device testing needs
#   an actual reachable address instead.
#
# Whatever you put here, the backend (apps/backend/.env's
# PUBLIC_BASE_URL) should normally match it — that's what magic-link
# emails use to build a clickable URL, and a link pointing at
# "localhost" is only clickable-and-working on the same machine that
# sent it.
WXT_REALTIME_URL=http://localhost:3001
